Ascomorpha is a genus of rotifers belonging to the family Gastropodidae. The genus has almost cosmopolitan distribution.Species:
Ascomorpha agilis Zacharias, 1893
Ascomorpha dumonti De Smet, 1992
Ascomorpha ecaudis Perty, 1850
Ascomorpha ovalis (Bergendahl, 1892)Species brought into synonymy
Ascomorpha ecaudatus Perty, 1850 : synonym of Ascomorpha ecaudis Perty, 1850